Class DnsTextEndpointGroupBuilder

      • ttl

        public final B ttl(int minTtl,
                   int maxTtl)
        Sets the minimum and maximum TTL of the DNS records (in seconds). If the TTL of the DNS record returned by the DNS server is less than the minimum TTL or greater than the maximum TTL, the TTL from the DNS server will be ignored and minTtl or maxTtl will be used respectively. The default minTtl and maxTtl are 1 and Integer.MAX_VALUE, which practically tells to respect the server TTL.

      • serverAddresses

        public final B serverAddresses(InetSocketAddress... serverAddresses)
        Sets the DNS server addresses to send queries to. Operating system default is used by default.

      • serverAddresses

        public final B serverAddresses(Iterable<InetSocketAddress> serverAddresses)
        Sets the DNS server addresses to send queries to. Operating system default is used by default.

      • backoff

        public final B backoff(Backoff backoff)
        Sets the Backoff that determines how much delay should be inserted between queries when a DNS server sent an error response. Backoff.exponential(1000, 32000).withJitter(0.2) is used by default.
